  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">2020 Iraq Crisis Appeal: Displacement Tracking Matrix (DTM) in Iraq</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The objective is to provide access to up-to-date, reliable and comprehensive information about internally displaced persons (IDP) and returnee populations in Iraq, as well as their needs and vulnerabilities. This is achieved through the implementation of IOM&#x2019;s Displacement Tracking Matrix (DTM) tool and timely dissemination of results to government authorities, UN Humanitarian Country Team (UNHCT) partners, non-governmental organisation NGOs, think tanks, media, academics and other stakeholders. The project will be implemented across Iraq and have the following key outputs: to increase access to displacement information through the distribution of DTM products; enhance regional and national government authorities&#x2019; data management capacities; and improve access to data for Clusters, including protection data to relevant cluster partners, and other relevant parties.</narrative>
  </description>
